  "title": "Kindergarten Care (KCare) Programme Staff (Teacher)",
  "description": "<p>Job Description</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Working in a before and after school care for MOE Kindergarten going children.</li>\n  <li>Caring for K1 &amp; K2 (5 to 6 years old children).</li>\n  <li>Modular activities with high leels of interaction with children: 1. Art &amp; Craft 2. Tinkering 3. Cookery 4. Music Movement &amp; Dramatisation 5. Gardening 6. Sand &amp; Water Play</li>\n  <li>No academic teaching involved.</li>\n  <li>Preparation of activities and field visits (if any)</li>\n  <li>Ensuring the safety and health standards, handling emergencies and setting up of a conducive environment for the children.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Job Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At the minimum, Student Care Centre (Early Years) Certificate.</li>\n  <li>Diploma in Early Childhood Care &amp; Education (DECCE-T) or an ECDA recognised equivalent obtained in the English medium preferred.</li>\n  <li>Required Skill(s): Classroom management, Lesson preparation, Activity planning, Teamwork and Coordination</li>\n  <li>Patient and caring personality.</li>\n  <li>Passion for children</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>",
